Class Player

java.lang.Object
javafx.scene.Node
javafx.scene.shape.Shape
javafx.scene.shape.Circle
developpement.Player
All Implemented Interfaces:
javafx.css.Styleable, javafx.event.EventTarget
public class Player extends javafx.scene.shape.Circle
The Player class is used to create a player object to use on the board, it inherits from the Circle class with all its attributes and methods. Most of the methods to interact with it are defined in the Board class.
Author:
Cardenas D, Ruellan B, Machnik A, Johnson A, Guenneau R
